			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Functional pop; Functional drinks; Health drinks,其他饮料（功能饮料）</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Functional pop; Functional drinks; Health drinks,其他饮料（功能饮料）</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Food and renewable raw materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A functional beverage is a conventional liquid food marketed to highlight specific product ingredients or supposed health benefits. These include dairy beverages, sports and performance drinks, energy drinks, ready-to-drink teas, 'smart' drinks, fortified fruit drinks, plant milks, and enhanced water. Bulgarian boza is an example of a functional beverage prepared from einkorn, wheat, and millet, among other mixtures of grains. Functional benefits in a beverage or food include immune-boosting, improving gut health, and heart health.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">功能性饮料是一种常规的液体食品，其营销重点是突出特定的产品成分或所声称的健康益处。这些包括乳制饮料、运动和表现饮料、能量饮料、即饮茶、'智能'饮料、强化果汁、植物奶和增强水。保加利亚的布扎酒是一种由小麦、大麦和谷物等混合物制成的功能性饮料的例子。饮料或食品的功能性益处包括增强免疫力、改善肠道健康和心脏健康。</common:generalComment>
